  "abstract": "A two-week national training course on Carbon Sequestration and Carbon Trading\r\nsupported by National Agricultural Innovation Project (NAIP) and Indian Council for\r\nAgricultural Research (ICAR) was held at ICRISAT-Patancheru from 6 to 17 February, 2012.\r\nSixteen participants representing ICAR institutions, State Agricultural Universities (SAUs),\r\nand ICRISAT participated in this course which was jointly offered by the ICRISAT, India\r\nand University of Florida, USA (Figure 1). The training was comprised of theory and handson\r\nexperiences by renowned faculty trainers from ICRISAT, the University of Florida,\r\nVirginia Tech University and the National Bureau of Soil Survey and Land Use Planning\r\n(NBSS&LUP), Nagpur. The course......",
